High level working:
Miner → Log → Dashboard → Touchscreen/Web

Requirements
Raspberry Pi (any model with Linux + Python 3.9+; tested on 3b but other should work as well)

RPi 7" touchscreen (or HDMI screen)

Python 3 with tkinter + requests

cpuminer (for actual hashing)

Internet access (for difficulty + block height)

A Bitcoin wallet address (bech32 recommended, e.g. bc1...)

Installation

Update system + dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-tk git curl \
    libjansson4 libjansson-dev automake autotools-dev build-essential
pip3 install requests pillow

Clone this repo
https://github.com/Retep1972/Raspberry-Pi-NerdMiner.git

Build cpuminer
git clone https://github.com/pooler/cpuminer.git
cd cpuminer
./autogen.sh
./configure CFLAGS="-O3"
make
cd ..

The miner binary will be in cpuminer/minerd.

Configuration

Service file for cpuminer
Create /etc/systemd/system/cpuminer.service:

[Unit]
Description=cpuminer (CPU lottery mining)
After=network-online.target
Wants=network-online.target

[Service]
User=pi
WorkingDirectory=/home/pi/rpi-nerdminer/cpuminer
ExecStart=/home/pi/rpi-nerdminer/cpuminer/minerd -a sha256d -o stratum+tcp://solo.ckpool.org:3333 -O "bc1qYOURWALLETADDRESS:x" --threads=2 
Restart=always
RestartSec=5
Nice=10
StandardOutput=append:/home/pi/.local/share/cpuminer.log
StandardError=append:/home/pi/.local/share/cpuminer.log

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Replace bc1qYOURWALLETADDRESS with your own wallet.
Adjust --threads depending on your Pi (2 threads is safe for a Pi 4).

Enable + start:
sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl enable cpuminer
sudo systemctl start cpuminer


Monitor logs:
journalctl -u cpuminer -f

Dashboard as a Service (autostart on boot)
Create a service file for the dashboard:

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/piminer-dashboard.service

Paste this (adjust paths to where your Python file lives):
[Unit]
Description=Pi Lottery Miner Dashboard
After=graphical.target

[Service]
User=pi
WorkingDirectory=/home/pi/rpi-nerdminer
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /home/pi/rpi-nerdminer/pi_lottery_miner.py
Restart=always
Environment=DISPLAY=:0
Environment=XAUTHORITY=/home/pi/.Xauthority

[Install]
WantedBy=graphical.target

Notes:
Replace pi if you’re running under another username.
DISPLAY=:0 assumes you’re running the standard Pi desktop on the touchscreen.

Enable and start it:
sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl enable piminer-dashboard
sudo systemctl start piminer-dashboard

if blockheight on dashboard shows: --
sudo apt install --reinstall ca-certificates -y
sudo update-ca-certificates

OPTIONAL Add screen_power_therm_guard.py and add it as a service to switch of backlight and reroute power to cpu. this service also monitors core temp and switches of if its getting to high
[Unit]
Description=RPi Touchscreen Power Saver + Overheat Guard
After=multi-user.target
Wants=multi-user.target

[Service]
Type=simple
# Root needed to write /sys/class/backlight/* and to power off
User=root
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /home/pi-miner/piminer/screen_power_therm_guard.py --idle-secs 300 --mode off --temp-threshold 80 --check-interval 30 --grace-reads 2 --log-file /var/log/pi_guard.log
Restart=always
RestartSec=2

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Enable and start it:
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable screen-power-therm-guard
sudo systemctl start screen-power-therm-guard
journalctl -u screen-power-therm-guard -f


